						               													<description>The Ultimate Trivia Boardgame! Triviavore highlights the brilliant absurdity of mother nature. But it also employs Darwinian survival strategies. You don&amp;rsquo;t need to know a thing about aardvarks to become an apex hunter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unlike some trivia games, this one offers you closed choices (&amp;ldquo;A, B, or C?&amp;rdquo;). So if a question stumps the central organ in your nervous system, you can frequently survive on hunches, or guessing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you think trivia questions are about as friendly as rattlesnakes, then go light on the gnarly questions. Find &amp;ldquo;camouflage and dodge&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;ink and stink&amp;rdquo; cards to build your defenses. Or land on a human to damage someone else&amp;rsquo;s habitat (or repair your own).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Triviavore takes two or three minutes to set up and 15-20 minutes to play. It is printed entirely in the USA on sustainably harvested paper certified by the Forest Stewardship Council. It has no plastic parts, and is not even shrink-wrapped. The cards celebrate nature and are colorful and attractive.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
